flow.mentorSays:
Let's understand what this Intercepting Routes challenge asks for.

**Challenge Description:**
// Modal on same page, full page on refresh

**What we need to build:**
This challenge tests your understanding of (.)folder convention.

**Time estimate:** 22 minutes
**Difficulty level:** Mid

**Expected Solution Overview:**
```typescript
// app/photos/[id]/page.tsx
export default function PhotoPage({
  params
}: {
  params: { id: string }
}) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Photo {params.id}</h1>
      <img src={`/photos/${params.id}.jpg`} alt="Photo" />
    </div>
  );
}

// app/photos/(.)photo/[id]/page.tsx
export default function...
```

This is a practical interview question that tests your understanding of core Angular concepts and your ability to implement them correctly.

Perfect! Here's the optimal solution approach:

```typescript
// app/photos/[id]/page.tsx
export default function PhotoPage({
  params
}: {
  params: { id: string }
}) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Photo {params.id}</h1>
      <img src={`/photos/${params.id}.jpg`} alt="Photo" />
    </div>
  );
}

// app/photos/(.)photo/[id]/page.tsx
export default function PhotoModal({
  params
}: {
  params: { id: string }
}) {
  return (
    <div className="modal">
      <h2>Photo {params.id} (Modal)</h2>
      <img src={`/photos/${params.id}.jpg`} alt="Photo" />
    </div>
  );
}
```

This solution demonstrates best practices for Nextjs development and shows how to properly implement (.)folder convention.

